com.elite.framework.server

Class ConnectedPlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.elite.framework.server.ConnectedPlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class ConnectedPlayer
extends java.lang.Thread
    A ConnectedPlayer object represents a player that is connected to the Server that owns it.

    This class contains the means by which to communicate with the player. i.e. the Socket, the input and output streams, the player's IP address ,and the port the player is sending/recieving UDP datagrams from.

    Author:
    Fraser Brooks

      • getAvailableMaps

        public java.lang.String[] getAvailableMaps()
        Player's might want to create and share their own maps. To prevent a host selecting a map that one player does not have, the list of available maps sent to the host is made up of only the maps that are present on all player's machines.
        Returns:
        - a String Array containing the list of maps that this player has on their machine
